# Documentation and user manual stay in sync

When you **add or materially change** operator-facing behavior documented in any of:

- `README.md`
- `FAQ.md`
- `PRD.md`
- `ENGINEERING.md`

also update **`USER_MANUAL.md`** with the equivalent **end-user / operator** steps and wording (what to click, permissions, limits, and cautions). Skip only if the change is **purely internal** (e.g. refactor with no UX impact) and no manual text would change.

When creating **new** top-level product docs in this repo that describe user-visible features, consider whether `USER_MANUAL.md` needs a matching section or cross-link.

This project treats the manual as part of the same documentation set as README/FAQ/PRD/ENGINEERING.
